      "patient_reported_reason": "Routine chronic disease review and medication check",
      "clinician_notes": "Subjective: 82-year-old female with multiple chronic conditions. Reports worsening ankle oedema over past 2 weeks. On furosemide 40 mg OD. Adherent to medications. No chest pain. No dizziness on standing noted recently.\n\nObjective: BP 148/90 mmHg, HR 78 bpm, Weight 71 kg (up 2 kg since last visit 3 months ago). SpO2 95% on RA. Pitting oedema both ankles ++. Chest: mild basal creps. eGFR 38 mL/min/1.73m2. Potassium 4.1 mmol/L.\n\nAssessment: CHF decompensation — likely fluid overload on furosemide. Hypertension not at target. CKD 3 stable.\n\nPlan: Increase fluid monitoring. Increase furosemide temporarily to 80 mg OD for 1 week then reduce to 40 mg. BP review — consider amlodipine up-titration. Annual medicines review referral.",
      "diagnoses": [
        {
          "code_system": "ICD-10", "code": "I50.9",
          "display": "Heart failure, unspecified",
          "status": "active", "certainty": "confirmed"
        },
