      "patient_reported_reason": "Follow-up — oedema and blood pressure",
      "clinician_notes": "Subjective: Improvement in ankle oedema after furosemide increase. Now back on 40 mg. BP still slightly elevated. No dizziness. Weight down 1.5 kg.\n\nObjective: BP 142/86 mmHg, HR 76 bpm, Weight 69.5 kg. Mild ankle oedema +. eGFR 37 mL/min (stable). Potassium 4.0 mmol/L.\n\nAssessment: CHF improving. BP partially controlled. CKD 3 stable.\n\nPlan: Increase amlodipine to 10 mg. Continue furosemide 40 mg. Annual review all medications in context of CKD. Bone health review for osteoporosis — consider calcium/D3 supplement (check vitamin D first).",
